## Root FS on typical HDD

check filesystem rootfs path /
    if SPACE usage > 95% for 10 cycles   then alert
    if inode usage > 95% for 10 cycles then alert
    if read rate > 250 operations/s for 10 cycles then alert
    if write rate > 250 operations/s for 10 cycles then alert
    if read rate > 200 MB/s for 10 cycles then alert
    if write rate > 200 MB/s for 10 cycles  then alert


## Additional FS on fast RAID or SSD 
# check filesystem datafs path /data
#    if SPACE usage > 95% for 10 cycles then alert
#    if inode usage > 95% for 10 cycles then alert
#    if read rate > 1500 operations/s for 10 cycles  then alert
#    if write rate > 1500 operations/s for 10 cycles  then alert
#    if read rate > 300 MB/s for 10 cycles then alert
#    if write rate > 300 MB/s for 10 cycles  then alert



